Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9. Boil a full #kettle{} of water.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Trim the @carrot{3}, then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

Pour the boiled water from your kettle into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

Add the potatoes to the water and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pop the @British Cumberland Sausages{8} and carrots onto a large #baking tray{} with a drizzle of @oil{}. Season the carrots with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until the carrots are tender and the sausages are browned and cooked through, ~{16-18%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw sausages. They're cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

In the meantime, halve any thick broccoli stems lengthways.

When about 10 mins of roasting time remain, add the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{80%grams} to the baking tray. Drizzle with @oil{}, season, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use another tray if necessary.

Roast for the remaining time until the broccoli is tender and crispy, ~{10-12%minutes}.

While everything roasts, pour the @water for the Jus{150%milliliter} into a small #saucepan{} and bring to the boil on high heat.

Stir in the @Red Wine Jus Paste{15%grams}, then reduce the heat to medium-high.

Allow the sauce to bubble and thicken, stirring regularly, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed, then remove from the heat and cover with a lid or foil to keep warm.

While the red wine jus simmers, trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{1}.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat. Add a knob of @butter{} and a splash of @milk{} (if you have any) to the potatoes, then mash until smooth.

Stir through the spring onion.

Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cover with a lid to keep warm.

Share the champ mash between your #plates{}.

Top with the sausages, then pour over the red wine jus (reheat first if needed).

Serve the roasted carrots and broccoli alongside. Enjoy!